    "name": "Honey And The Bees",
    "profile": "The Honey and the Bees line up that is known for the output from 1966 to 1972 is Nadine Felder White, Cassandra Ann Wooten, Jean Davis Sanders and Gwen Oliver (later known as Gwen Wesley).  Most of these members were in a group called [a871431].  They went on to audition for producer [a319842] and recorded a single [r=9432849] which was released In 1965.They were named Honey And The Bees by [a987850] following their audition for him. An article on the Philadelphia Neighborhoods website February 29, 2012 mentions that when Felder was added, for a brief period of time, they were called Sugar and Spice and then they became Honey & the Bees.  \r\n\r\nAs Honey & the Bees, their recorded output  began in 1966 with a release on the [l84482] label. Releasing at least fourteen singles, which included five on  Arctic and six on [l33569], as well as an album, they also had a hit in 1971 with \"It's Gonna Take a Miracle\" . The A side of what appears to be their final single, [m=1012827]\"  is a Phil Hur",
